  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to establish a diagnosis in transient global amnesia (TGA) in
      assessing three episodic memory's abilities (mental simulation throught the future, and the
      past, the learning of personnal actions i-e the enactment effect). Secondary goal is to
      describe the neuronal substrates associated to the alteration of theses abilites in TGA.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
